Thank you for relying on Siemens quality and for choosing Automation Designer as your solution for electrical and automation engineering.

Automation Designer is intended for electrical engineers and automation engineers from the discrete industry who work in teams on multi-disciplinary projects. By focusing on re-usability, rule-based engineering, and cross-discipline collaboration and data integration, Automation Designer improves the consistency of such projects, reduces the time and cost invested in them, and increases the productivity of the entire production engineering process.
variations: Automation Designer is a Digital Factory solution for electrical and automation engineering. It lets you design the electrical and automation solution for a production system or machine, eventually enabling the generation of its electrical schematics and PLC program. Can also work with other automation products like Line Designer.

Although Automation Designer can be used as a stand-alone application, engineering for the digital factory is always a multi-disciplinary effort.

Automation Designer is integrated in the Siemens software portfolio for the digital factory, which offers a broad range of solutions for discrete industries.

True to Siemens' vision for the digital factory, these solutions provide a fast and seamless transition between the involved departments and engineering disciplines. They parallelize operational processes and optimize interactions and data integration.

Within this chain of software solutions, Line Designer, Automation Designer, and Process Simulate form the Integrated Mechatronics Engineering Suite.

You can create template in different ways:
To do this, insert an existing template into a project, modify it, and then turn it into a new template

1. Choose File tab-> New Item. 
2. In the New Item dialog box, click the Automation Designer tab. 
3. In the Templates group, select the Template row. 
4. In the Attributes group, in the ID row, double-click the Value cell. 
5. In the Type dialog box, expand the tree and select a type. 
6. Click OK. 
Automation Designer opens the template environment.
7. In the template environment, build your template.
8. Choose File tab->Save Template . 
9. Choose File tab->Close->Close Template.

1. Open the project whose engineering data you want to reuse.
2. In the project, choose Home tab->Reuse Operations group->Create Template. 
3. Hold Ctrl or Shift as you select the objects that you want to add to the template in the navigators. 
4. In the Name group, type the name and description of the template. 
5. Click OK -> Template environment is open.
6. Modify the template as necessary.
7. Choose File tab->Save Template -> The Save Template dialog displays. 
8. In the Classification dialog box, expand the tree and select a classification class and subclass. 
9. Click OK.

1. Choose the Home tab, Electrical Engineering tab, or Controller Programming tab->Insert group->Template 
2. In the Reuse Library, expand the Solution Library node and select the required node. 
3. In the Select Member panel, select a suitable template. 
4. In the Template dialog box, in the Aspects group, click Select Parent . 
5. In the corresponding Aspect Navigator, select the Engineering Object under which you want to insert the root node of the template.
6. Click OK.
